<p><b>Summary executions;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged extrajudicial killings by the Nigerian Security Forces. According to 
the information received, Boko Haram, a group operating in northern 
Nigeria, has launched scaled terror attacks across Nigeria. Reportedly, since 
mid-2009, as a tactic of response to fight this group, extrajudicial 
executions, enforced disappearance, torture and detention without trial 
against persons known to be members of this group and those suspected to 
be helping or sympathizing with them have been performed by the Nigerian 
Security forces. Moreover, it is alleged that incidents unrelated to the fight 
against Boko Haram have also occurred, including killings by police 
officers of Umoar Danmichika and Lucy Ukpong. 
