Rashoudi held a meeting in Riyadh where he reportedly publicly asserted 
that the rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association are 
legitimate and internationally recognized. On 12 December 2012, he was 
reportedly arrested while he was on his way to the Qassim region. The 
Saudi Interior Ministry purportedly used a verdict from 2011 to arrest and 
detain Mr Al Rashoudi. Mr. Al Rashoudi is also a defendant in a case which 
reached the appeal stage. In this case, he was convicted of involvement in 
