<p><b>Extreme poverty;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;  Migrants;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged limitations on access to justice for migrant farmworkers in fourteen 
states of the U.S.A. According to information received, lack of legislation 
and implementation of existing legislation enables the detrimental nation-
wide practice of denying or not allowing certain human rights defenders, in 
particular legal advocates and other community service providers, 
meaningful access to migrant farmworker in labor camps, including by 
allegedly harassing and threatening these human rights advocates.  
</p>
