<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;   
</b></p>
<p>Alleged lack of compliance of new law on peaceful assembly with 
international standards related to freedom of peaceful assembly and to 
freedom of opinion and expression. According to the information received, 
a new law on peaceful assembly (Law no. 65/2012), which aims at 
regulating peaceful protests, was recently passed by the Libyan General 
National Congress. It is reported that several provisions contained in the law 
would unduly restrict the right to freedom of peaceful assembly, which may 
in turn also lead to restrictions of freedom of opinion and expression. 
</p>
<p> 
 
 
 
 
 
 
</p>
<p> 
09/01/2013 
JAL 
 
