</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;  Summary 
</b></p>
<p><b>executions;  Violence 
</b></p>
<p><b>against women;   
</b></p>
<p>Alleged killing of two women human rights defenders. According to the 
information received, Ms. Montha Chukaew and Ms. Pranee Boonrat, both 
members of the Southern Peasants' Federation of Thailand (SPFT) left their 
community of Khlong Sai Pattana, Surat Thani province in the morning of 
19 November 2012 and were fatally shot by unknown individuals not far 
from the village. As members of the SPFT, Ms. Chukaew and Ms. Boonrat 
were involved in a land rights dispute between their community and a palm 
oil company. The Khlong Sai Pattana community has reportedly been the 
target of previous violent incidents including threats and intimidation which 
are believed to be related to the community's land rights activities.  
