was arrested and detained on 4 January 2013 by members of the armed 
forces while filming a report for Reuters in a military zone in Rafah near the 
Egyptian-Gaza border. Mr. Sabry was allegedly prevented from contacting 
his lawyer and his family before being placed into detention. He was 
charged with trespassing and filming in a prohibited military zone (Articles 
80(e)2 and 80(e)4 of the Penal Code), and at the time the communication 
was sent, he was detained at the Central Prison of Arish and was scheduled 
to appear before a military court on 9 January 2013. Mr. Bassem Youssef, a 
satirist and host of a CBC TV show El-Bernameg, was under investigation 
on charges of denigrating the head of state. Complaints were also reportedly 
filed against the daily newspaper Al-Masri Al-Youm and several of its 
