efsad-e fel arz (&#8213;sowing corruption on earth&#8214;), &#8213;gathering and colluding 
against State security&#8214; and &#8213;spreading propaganda against the system&#8214;, 
which are not considered as most serious crimes under international law, 
following a trial that allegedly did not comply with international human 
rights law provisions of fair trial and due process.   
